Scenario:
Implement a multi-tier customer support system where support tickets are escalated based on their complexity. The system should automatically route a request through a chain of help desks until it finds a handler capable of resolving it.

Requirements:

Request Object: SupportRequest containing the issue's priority or type.

Base Handler: SupportHandler (Abstract Class) that holds a reference to the next handler in the chain.

Concrete Handlers:

Chatbot: Handles basic, low-level queries.

TechTeam: Handles intermediate technical issues.

SeniorEngineer: Handles critical or complex architectural problems.

Goal: Decouple the sender of a request from its receivers by giving more than one object a chance to handle the request.